                            <comment id="17526675" author="emilles" created="Fri, 22 Apr 2022 20:48:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;tt&gt;StringBuilder#substring&lt;/tt&gt; is a public method from the package-private superclass &lt;tt&gt;AbstractStringBuilder&lt;/tt&gt;.  The necessary accommodations have been made in Groovy 4.  It is unclear at this time if we will backport to Groovy 3.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17684222" author="emilles" created="Sat, 4 Feb 2023 23:25:10 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Can you retry using the latest Groovy 3 snapshot? The java compiler creates public bridge methods in &lt;tt&gt;StringBuilder&lt;/tt&gt; and &lt;tt&gt;StringBuffer&lt;/tt&gt; for the public methods of &lt;tt&gt;AbstractStringBuilder&lt;/tt&gt; (the package-private super class). A change was rolled back in the type checker so that the bridge methods regain preference. I don&apos;t know if the meta-object protocol (MOP &#8211; the runtime selection algorithms) do the same.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Update: demo project still fails with Groovy 3.0.15-SNAPSHOT and Java 17.0.4.1 for me. Add this to your &lt;tt&gt;build.gradle&lt;/tt&gt; repositories section:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-groovy&quot;&gt;
maven { url = &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&apos;https:&lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;//groovy.jfrog.io/artifactory/libs-snapshot-local/&apos;&lt;/span&gt; }&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17684335" author="emilles" created="Sun, 5 Feb 2023 18:30:25 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/groovy/commit/b20e31d721ecd4348358103b47bd69a0e718c8c4&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/groovy/commit/b20e31d721ecd4348358103b47bd69a0e718c8c4&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
